Gapminder

For this assignment, we are going to use data from gapminder. Gapminder includes information about economics, population, social issues, and life expectancy from countries all over the world. We will use three data sets, so please load all three.

One thing to note is that the data include years beyond 2021. These are projections based on modeling done by the gapminder organization. Start by importing the data.

t_lifeexp %>% 
  filter(year>=1920,year<=2020) %>% 
  group_by(country) %>% 
  summarize(meanlife=mean(life_exp,na.rm=T),.groups="keep") %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=reorder(country,meanlife), y=meanlife))+
  geom_col()+
  theme_classic(base_family="Avenir")+
  theme(axis.text.x=element_text(size=8,angle=30,hjust=1),
        plot.title = element_text(size = 10, hjust = 0.5),
        axis.title = element_text(size = 8))+
  labs(title="Average Life Expectancy Between 1920-2020 of 187 Countries",
       x="Country",
       y="Average Life Expectancy (Years)")+
  scale_x_discrete(breaks = c("Mali","Brazil","Andorra"))
